The paper deals with the task of generating high-resolution images from low-resolution inputs, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves using a generative adversarial network (GAN) with a latent space and perceptual loss, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of natural images and subspaces, which are relevant to graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
